High-level architecture for BFSI “Intent Firewall” (Loan Application)
Here’s a clear, component‑level view you can turn into a diagram in Draw.io, Miro, Lucidchart, etc.

1. Components
Client layer

Mobile/Web App

Loan application UI (forms, document upload, free‑text fields).

Edge & access layer

API Gateway / Load Balancer

Handles routing, auth, TLS termination.

Forwards loan‑related traffic to the AI Intent Firewall Sidecar instead of directly to core services.

AI intent firewall layer (your product)

AI Sidecar Service

Receives the full loan application request (metadata + payload).

Calls internal services and AI models to evaluate risk and intent.

Feature & Context Enrichment Service

Fetches:

User profile

Device fingerprint

Geo/IP info

Historical behavior (past loans, rejections, fraud flags)

Builds a context object for AI.

AI Risk & Intent Engine

Uses LLM + rules + anomaly detection to produce:

risk_score

intent (e.g., “genuine”, “possible fraud”, “synthetic identity”)

action (ALLOW / BLOCK / ESCALATE / CHALLENGE)

reason (explainability).

Policy Decision Point (PDP)

Applies bank‑defined policies on top of AI output.

Final decision: what to do with this request.

Policy Enforcement Point (PEP)

Enforces decision:

Forward to core loan service

Return error/denial

Trigger extra verification

Route to manual review.

Core banking & loan layer

Loan Origination Microservice

Normal loan processing logic (scoring, eligibility, workflow).

KYC/AML Systems

Existing identity and compliance checks.

Core Banking System

Accounts, balances, existing loans, etc.

Support systems

Fraud & Risk Analytics

Receives logs and decisions for offline analysis.

Monitoring & Logging

Observability for AI sidecar + loan flow.

Model Management

Versioning, A/B testing, monitoring of AI models.

2. Request flow (step by step)
User submits loan application  
Mobile/Web App → POST /loan/apply.

API Gateway receives request

Authenticates user.

Routes loan traffic to AI Intent Firewall Sidecar.

AI Sidecar ingests request

Parses payload (form fields, free text, metadata).

Context enrichment

Sidecar calls:

User profile service

Device/geo service

Historical behavior service

KYC/AML flags

Builds a rich context object.

AI risk & intent evaluation

Context + payload → AI Risk & Intent Engine.

Engine returns:

risk_score, intent, reason, recommended_action.

Policy decision

PDP applies bank policies:

Example:

If risk_score < 40 → ALLOW

If 40–80 → ESCALATE

If > 80 → BLOCK

Policy enforcement

If ALLOW → forward original request to Loan Origination Microservice.

If ESCALATE → route to manual review queue / trigger extra KYC.

If BLOCK → return denial response to client with generic message.

Core loan processing

Loan Origination Microservice runs as usual (no change in its code).

Downstream calls to KYC, credit bureau, core banking, etc.

Logging & analytics

AI decision + context + outcome logged to:

Fraud/Risk Analytics

Monitoring/observability stack.
